5C%22%3EA%202020%20study%20in%20Nature%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20machine%20learning%20models%20could%20reduce%20the%20time%20it%20took%20to%20identify%20a%20fast-charging%20battery%20design%20from%20500%20days%20to%2016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20we're%20solving%20is%20really%20to%20speed%20up%20the%20pace%20of%20battery%20development%2C%26quot%3B%20Koeller%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20this%20would%20be%20crucial%20to%20producing%20EVs%20that%20can%20hold%20their%20own%20against%20combustion-engine%20counterparts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20definitely%20going%20to%20need%20significantly%20better%20battery%20performance%20and%20it's%20our%20belief%20that%20the%20way%20that%20we%20get%20there%20is%20by%20doing%20battery%20development%20in%20a%20fundamentally%20different%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f50cf130-8c6d-4c06-88f7-4cd95c5ec07b%5C%22%3EBoosting%20batteries%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDesigning%20EV%20batteries%20is%20a%20three-step%20process%2C%20Georgia%20Tech%20assistant%20professor%20Micah%20Ziegler%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EScientists%20must%20first%20decide%20on%20a%20structure%20and%20combination%20of%20elements%20that%20will%20produce%20a%20battery%20material%20with%20the%20desired%20properties%20before%20developing%20a%20recipe%20to%20synthesize%20it%20and%20testing%20that%20material%20in%20a%20lab.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sheer%20number%20of%20potential%20combinations%20and%20the%20variety%20of%20demands%20placed%20on%20EV%20batteries%20%E2%80%94%20including%20longevity%2C%20safety%2C%20cost%2C%20and%20charging%20speed%20%E2%80%94%20makes%20designing%20batteries%20a%20lengthy%20and%20difficult%20process%2C%20Ziegler%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20number%20of%20options%20is%20just%20vast.%20Once%20you%20start%20putting%20different%20elements%20together%2C%20we're%20talking%20about%20potentially%20trillions%20of%20different%20combinations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAI%20could%